event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_03819ae70075d67c016a049e70b184819c8e8e3839c482852d","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":472,"text":"First train (from Paris) goes 80 km/h from 3:00. By 4:00 it has gone 80 km, so the remaining distance between the trains is 470 − 80 = 390 km.\n\nTheir closing speed is 80 + 100 = 180 km/h, so time to meet after 4:00 is 390/180 = 13/6 h = 2 h 10 min.\n\nThey meet at 4:00 + 2:10 = 6:10 pm.  \nDistance from Paris = first train's total travel = 80 × (1 + 13/6) = 80 × 19/6 = 760/3 km = 253 1/3 km."}

